	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Trolls rock as warriors - Strong and tough(though not as good starting stats as ogres) they have nightvision and the king of all warrior attributes...  Regeneration.  The downtime is much much quicker with Trolls.  My basic points would be start ruckin outside of grobb near the guards, get to 2nd by taking evens, leave the kobolds and froggies (apart from tads) alone till 2nd.  It wont take long cos of your low hps and good regen you can pretty much fight non stop. Be on the lookout for decaying skelies with weapons, these A) sell well for newbies and B) will allow you train up in other modes of combat.  If you have a 2 handed weapon then use that for tough stuff (even/yello) and use the 1hs for blues, that way you get your two main weapon skills in constant use.  You do this so that at 13 you can go dual wield with no problem with weapon skills (I had major problems with my ogre cos his 1hs was poor and thus his dual wield was cruddy too).  If you take a look around you can get some pretty nice stuff for a new character around in Grobb or Oggok.  Feerott is to the left from Grobb (dont follow the wall straight away cos theres a nasty very red bard who will kick your harris) and Guk is to the right (or South ro if u pass Guk).  Guk is the froggy city and you will find more n more froggies around as u approach it.   If theyre blue or higher to you and nearby when your fighting one, they WILL join in.  But fortunately the Guk zone is quite close and u can leg it in there and rest up.  The guards outside are around 4/6th lvl and give good xp.  There are some crocs inside that are very good xp for 10th-12th and not too tuff (singly) for a troll with a good 2handed wep.  If you pass guk and head to the south ro zone, theres foragers and kobold hunters of around 6th -8th and swamp and bull alligators up there too.  You dont actually need to go to another zone for quite some time if u dont want to because Innothule has it all for upto 10th.  Feerott however is a good place to pop to every now and then to releive the gloominess of the swamp and the lil brood and hatchlings look so cute.  
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
